{{Infobox recurring event | name =Beton Fest | native_name = | native_name_lang = | logo = File:Beton.fest.jpg | logo_alt = | logo_caption = | logo_size = | image = | image_size = | alt = | caption = | status = active | genre = [[Art festival]] | date = <!-- {{start date|YYYY|mm|dd}} "dates=" also works, but do not use both --> | begins = <!-- {{start date|YYYY|mm|dd}} --> | ends = <!-- {{end date|YYYY|mm|dd}} --> | frequency = <!-- Weekly, Monthly, Quarterly, Semi-annually, Annually, Bi-annually, 2nd Tuesday of November, etc. --> | venue = | location = Sarajevo | coordinates = <!-- {{coord|LAT|LON|type:event|display=inline,title}} --> | country = Bosnia and Herzegovina | years_active = 2012 - present | first = <!-- {{start date|YYYY|mm|dd}} "founded=" and "established=" also work --> | founder_name = <!-- or | founders = --> | last = <!-- Date of most recent event; if the event will not be held again, use {{End date|YYYY|MM|DD|df=y}} --> | prev = | next = | participants = | attendance = | capacity = | area = | budget = | activity = | leader_name = | patron = | organised = <!-- "organized=" also works --> | filing = | people = | member = | sponsor = <!-- | or sponsors = --> | website = {{URL|http://www.betonfest.com.ba}} | footnotes = }} '''Beton Fest''' is an international [[Three-dimensional space|3D]] [[street art]] [[festival]] held annually in [[Sarajevo]], [[Bosnia and Herzegovina]]. <ref>{{cite web|url=http://ba.n1info.com/a57856/Lifestyle/Poceo-Beton-Fest-u-Sarajevu.html|title=Beton Fest čini Sarajevo 3D prijestlonicom svijeta|publisher=N1 Television}}</ref> <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.alu.unsa.ba/content/beton-fest-u-sarajevu|title=Beton fest u Sarajevu|publisher=alu.unsa.ba}}</ref> It is held in July of every year and lasts for five days, bringing in international street artists from all over the world. <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.radiosarajevo.ba/metromahala/kultura/zvanicno-zatvoren-cetvrti-beton-fest-u-sarajevu/199304|title=Zvanično zatvoren četvrti Beton Fest u Sarajevu|publisher=Radio Sarajevo}}</ref> It was established in 2012 by the arts association ''Progres'' in cooperation with the Academy of Fine Arts, Sarajevo. <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.klix.ba/magazin/kultura/otvoren-konkurs-za-drugi-festival-street-art-umjetnosti-betonfest-sarajevo/130805004|title=Otvoren konkurs za učešće na drugom Beton Festu|publisher=klix.ba}}</ref> Apart from showcasing 3D street art, it also organizes the ''Beton Music Stage'' which holds concerts and open-air parties for the duration of the festival. <ref>{{cite web|url=http://novi.ba/clanak/30566/beton-fest-3d-crtezi-na-trgu-djece-sarajeva-odusevili-prolaznike|title=Beton Fest: 3D crteži na Trgu djece Sarajeva oduševili prolaznike|publisher=novi.ba}}</ref> It is the only 3D street art festival in Southeastern Europe <ref>{{cite web|url=http://ba.n1info.com/a57856/Lifestyle/Poceo-Beton-Fest-u-Sarajevu.html|title=Beton Fest čini Sarajevo 3D prijestlonicom svijeta|publisher=N1 Television}}</ref> and has hosted many renowned street artists such as Vera Bugatti <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.verabugatti.it/3d-street-art-on-peace-in-sarajevo/|title=3D street art on Peace in Sarajevo|publisher=verabugatti.it}}</ref>, Giovanna la Pietra <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.klix.ba/magazin/cijelo-sarajevo-je-pozvano-na-beton-fest/120612023|title=Cijelo Sarajevo pozvano na Beton Fest|publisher=klix.ba}}</ref>, Tony Cuboliquido <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cuboliquido.com/|title=3D street painting festival in Sarajevo|publisher=cuboliquido.com}}</ref>, Manuel Bastante <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.radiosarajevo.ba/metromahala/kultura/sarajevo-jos-samo-pet-dana-do-cetvrtog-beton-festa/198387|title=Sarajevo: Još samo pet dana do četvrtog Beton Festa|publisher=Radio Sarajevo}}</ref> and others.
