'''Wicked Faire''' was a yearly adult-themed fair with programming geared towards ages 16 and up. <ref>[http://wickedfaire.com/about Wicked Faire About Page]</ref> The last Wicked Faire, Wicked Faire: Reborn<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://wickedfaire.com/|title=Wicked Faire: Reborn - Wicked Winter Renaissance Faire|website=Wicked Winter Renaissance Faire|language=en-US|access-date=2018-03-20}}</ref>, was February 2-4, 2018 in Piscataway, NJ.  This event was created by and run by Widdershins, INC, d/b/a Jeff Mach Events. 

==2018 Performances and Panels==

*Mr. Person
*Tammy Shipps
*ZEN Productions
*Sharp Pleasures
*The Graces
*Voltaire
*A Halo Called Fred

==Controversy==

In January 2018, former volunteers and employees of Wicked Faire and other events organized by Jeff Mach Events (JME) accused JME founder Jeff Mach of sexual misconduct and questionable practices surrounding volunteer and employee compensation and event safety.<ref>https://owleyeview.blogspot.com/2018/01/time-to-name-drop-and-protect-newbies.html?m=1</ref> 

A new company, Silver Phoenix Society, attempted to purchase the intellectual property from Widdershins. Tammy Shipps, the president of Silver Phoenix and one of the panel presenters at Wicked Faire: Reborn, purchased the IP on March 13, 2018. <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/SilverPhoenixOrg/posts/1733603456725057|title=Silver Phoenix Society|website=www.facebook.com|language=en|access-date=2018-03-20}}</ref>


